Package acceptance

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    AcceptanceOmega
    Generic interface for an omega-regular acceptance condition (BitSet-based).
    AcceptanceOmegaDD
    Generic interface for an omega-regular acceptance condition (BDD-based).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    AcceptanceBuchi
    A Büchi acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets).
    AcceptanceBuchiDD
    A Büchi acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets).
    AcceptanceGeneric
    A generic acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets).
    AcceptanceGenericDD
    A generic acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets).
    AcceptanceGenRabin
    A Generalized Rabin acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets) This is a list of GenRabinPairs, which can be manipulated with the usual List interface.
    AcceptanceGenRabin.GenRabinPair
    A pair in a Generalized Rabin acceptance condition, i.e., with (F G !"L") & (G F "K_1") & ...
    AcceptanceGenRabinDD
    A Generalized Rabin acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets) This is a list of GenRabinPairs, which can be manipulated with the usual List interface.
    AcceptanceGenRabinDD.GenRabinPairDD
    A pair in a Generalized Rabin acceptance condition, i.e., with (F G !"L") & (G F "K_1") & ...
    AcceptanceOmega.LiftBitSet
    Abstract functor for use with the lift function.
    AcceptanceRabin
    A Rabin acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets).
    AcceptanceRabin.RabinPair
    A pair in a Rabin acceptance condition, i.e., with (F G !"L") & (G F "K")
    AcceptanceRabinDD
    A Rabin acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets) This is a list of RabinPairs, which can be manipulated with the usual List interface.
    AcceptanceRabinDD.RabinPairDD
    A pair in a Rabin acceptance condition, i.e., with (F G !"L") & (G F "K")
    AcceptanceReach
    A reachability acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets).
    AcceptanceReachDD
    A reachability acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets).
    AcceptanceStreett
    A Streett acceptance condition (based on BitSet state sets).
    AcceptanceStreett.StreettPair
    A pair in a Streett acceptance condition, i.e., with (G F "R") -> (G F "G")
    AcceptanceStreettDD
    A Streett acceptance condition (based on JDD state sets).
    AcceptanceStreettDD.StreettPairDD
    A pair in a Streett acceptance condition, i.e., with (G F "R") -> (G F "G")
